25 (6) "Mental health crisis" means a situation in which an individual's
26 emotional or mental state becomes so severe that it puts the individual at
27 risk of harming himself, herself, or others, prevents the individual from
28 properly caring for himself, herself, or significantly disrupts the
29 individual's ability to function in daily life.
30
31 23-99-1902. Mental health crisis — Prior authorization or
32 precertification for healthcare service prohibited.
33 A health benefit plan shall not require prior authorization or
34 precertification for a healthcare service provided by a healthcare provider
35 to an individual who is suffering a mental health crisis.
